## 📋 Instructions

> **ℹ️ Document Workflow Instructions**
> 
> **Section 1:** The business owner and sponsor complete Section 1 of this PRD. This will inform different teams of the business outcome expected.
> 
> **Section 2:** The Cross-Operations Leads (quoting, subscriptions, order management, supply chain, finance, etc.) will complete Section 2 of this PRD to provide additional information concerning operations and compliance needs.
> 
> **Section 3:** The testing lead, with input from operations teams, completes section 3 which will specify the UAT testing needs and duration that will be required and any other testing requests that should be factored into the overall planning.
> 
> **Section 4:** Teams will validate the BRD for completeness and perform an initial assessment of feasibility and accordingly may request Sections 1, 2 or 3 to be updated. Once the BRD has been validated, Teams will complete section 4 to identify teams and assets that will be required to design, build & implement the solution.
> 
> **Reference:** The final version of the PRD will be used as the final locked scope for planning purposes. Additional changes post scope lock will require change requests which may need to be planned for a subsequent release and/or change the timeline for delivery.

